                            <table class="tool-bench-table">
                                <tbody data-bench-tbl>
                                    <tr data-bench-row="seed"><td>Seed / Pre-A</td><td>60&ndash;100%</td></tr>
                                    <tr data-bench-row="series_a"><td>Series A</td><td>45&ndash;75%</td></tr>
                                    <tr data-bench-row="series_bc"><td>Series B&ndash;C</td><td>35&ndash;55%</td></tr>
                                    <tr data-bench-row="pe"><td>PE-backed</td><td>25&ndash;40%</td></tr>
                                    <tr data-bench-row="enterprise"><td>Enterprise</td><td>18&ndash;32%</td></tr>
                                </tbody>
                            </table>
                            <div class="tool-bench-note text-tiny">Ranges informed by KeyBanc SaaS Survey (2024), OpenView Benchmarks (2024), Bessemer State of the Cloud (2024), and GST engagement experience (2023&ndash;2025). Benchmarks are reviewed annually. Individual results vary based on business model and organizational structure.</div>
                            <div class="tool-bench-note text-tiny" data-industry-disc>These benchmarks are derived primarily from SaaS company data. Companies operating marketplace, fintech, infrastructure, or hardware-intensive models may observe materially different cost structures. Apply professional judgment when benchmarking outside a pure-SaaS context.</div>
